  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Channel
    Represents a twitch channel that can go live.
    ChannelPointReward
    Represents a twitch channel point reward.
    Chat
    Represents the chat of a Channel.
    ChatBadge
    Represents a twitch chat badge.
    Clip
    Represents a clip of a live stream.
    Emote
    Represents a twitch chat emote.
    HypeTrain
    Represents a hype train which occurs when a stream has got a set amount of subscriptions / cheers.
    IDable<T>
    Marks classes of which instances can have an id.
    Message
    Represents a chat message.
    Stream
    Represents a live stream.
    StreamSchedule
    Represents a stream schedule.
    StreamScheduleSegment
    Represents a stream schedule segment.
    Team
    Represents a twitch team.
    Updatable
    Marks classes that can be updated.
    User
    Represents a twitch user.
    Video
    Represents a twitch video.
